      <acqinfo encodinganalog="541">
         <head>Provenance</head>
         <p> The papers of Joseph Benson Foraker, army officer, governor of Ohio,
		  and United States Senator from Ohio, were given to the Library of Congress by
		  Julia B. Foraker in 1926 and 1931. </p>
      </acqinfo>
