      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
         <p> The papers of Joseph Benson Foraker (1846-1917) span the years
		  1884-1916 and consist of correspondence documenting his career as a judge,
		  governor, and United States senator from Ohio.</p>
         <p>The Foraker Papers include volumes of his correspondence to and from
		  Marcus Alonzo Hanna, Theodore Roosevelt, John Sherman, and William H. Taft
		  printed by the Foraker family. Also in the collection is a single volume of
		  original correspondence with other politicians and notables. The papers detail
		  the politics of the day and infighting within the Republican party. </p>
      </scopecontent>
